  32:../Backend/gnu-efi-3.0.9/lib/hw.c **** 
  33:../Backend/gnu-efi-3.0.9/lib/hw.c ****     Check to see if DevicePath exists for a given Protocol. Return Error if it
  34:../Backend/gnu-efi-3.0.9/lib/hw.c ****     exists. Return GlobalIoFuncs set match the DevicePath
  35:../Backend/gnu-efi-3.0.9/lib/hw.c **** 
  36:../Backend/gnu-efi-3.0.9/lib/hw.c ****   Arguments:
  37:../Backend/gnu-efi-3.0.9/lib/hw.c **** 
  38:../Backend/gnu-efi-3.0.9/lib/hw.c ****     DevicePath      - to operate on
  39:../Backend/gnu-efi-3.0.9/lib/hw.c ****     Protocol        - to check the DevicePath against
  40:../Backend/gnu-efi-3.0.9/lib/hw.c ****     ErrorStr        - ASCII string to display on error
  41:../Backend/gnu-efi-3.0.9/lib/hw.c ****     GlobalIoFncs    - Returned with DeviceIoProtocol for the DevicePath
  42:../Backend/gnu-efi-3.0.9/lib/hw.c **** 
  43:../Backend/gnu-efi-3.0.9/lib/hw.c **** Returns:
  44:../Backend/gnu-efi-3.0.9/lib/hw.c **** 
  45:../Backend/gnu-efi-3.0.9/lib/hw.c ****     Pass or Fail based on  wether GlobalIoFncs where found
  46:../Backend/gnu-efi-3.0.9/lib/hw.c **** 
  47:../Backend/gnu-efi-3.0.9/lib/hw.c **** --*/
